<subSubSection id="C3276CE6FFC2FFA9FF645F176371FEA9" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFC2FFA7FF645F17663BFB1C" blockId="7.[151,1436,1137,1233]" box="[151,282,1137,1161]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFC2FFA7FF345FF36300FB44" blockId="7.[151,1436,1137,1233]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
There are no extant specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFC2FFA7FDB75FF065FEFB38" authorityName=": Jolivet, Verma &amp; Mille" authorityYear="2003" box="[580,735,1173,1197]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caledonica">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FDB75FF065FEFB38" box="[580,735,1173,1197]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. caledonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except possibly a wing (not seen). The species was independently described twice, therefore we provide translations of the two descriptions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFC2FFA7FF645E6763A5FA8C" blockId="7.[151,1436,1281,1809]" box="[151,1156,1281,1305]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Translation of description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFC2FFA7FE2F5E67644BFA8C" authority="Jolivet, 1957" authorityName="Fauvel MS (Jolivet" authorityYear="1957" box="[476,874,1281,1305]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stenomela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caledonica">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FE2F5E6765F3FA8C" box="[476,722,1281,1305]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Stenomela caledonica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC429CFFC2FFA7FD2A5E67644BFA8C" author="Jolivet" box="[729,874,1281,1305]" firstAuthor="Jolivet" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 180" refId="ref21340" refString="Jolivet, P. (1957) Recherches sur l'aile des Chrysomeloidea (Coleoptera). Premiere partie. Memoires de l'Institut royale des Sciences naturelles de Belgique, 2 (51), 1 - 180." type="journal article" year="1957">Jolivet, 1957</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(page 59) [see 
<figureCitation id="130623E8FFC2FFA7FBE55E676359FA8C" box="[1046,1144,1281,1305]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="21.[151,258,1906,1927]" captionTargetBox="[189,1408,187,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-73@21.[179,1408,183,1882]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Bohumiljania caledonica (Jolivet). Figs 1–3, reproductions of original drawings of the holotype by Monrós (1958): 1, head &amp; pronotum; 2, ventral, with antenna; 3, lateral. Reproduced from Acta Zoologica Lilloana. Fig. 4, reproduction of original drawing of the wing of the holotype (Jolivet 1957). Reproduced from Mémoires de l’Institut royale des Sciences naturelles de Belgique." pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figure 4</figureCitation>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFC2FFA7FF345E43652EFA64" blockId="7.[151,1436,1281,1809]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
“We must note here that a curious undescribed genus of Chrysomeloidea has been discovered by us in the Fauvel collection (material from 
<collectingCountry id="F32A7FFDFFC2FFA7FE165E2C65BBFAF4" box="[485,666,1353,1377]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
). This insect was labelled, in the handwriting of the French author, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFC2FFA7FF525E0B66BBFA10" authority="MS" authorityName="Fauvel MS (Jolivet" authorityYear="1957" box="[161,410,1389,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stenomela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caledonica">Stenomela caledonica</taxonomicName>
” MS name. Certainly it has much external similarity with the neotropical genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFC2FFA7FADB5E0B62BAFA10" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1847" box="[1320,1435,1389,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stenomela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FADB5E0B62BAFA10" box="[1320,1435,1389,1413]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Stenomela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it will be described in a study of the New Caledonian fauna. We give below the description of the wing of “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFC2FFA7FF525ED3663AFA58" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1847" box="[161,283,1461,1485]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stenomela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Stenomela</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFC2FFA7FEDE5ED36689FA58" authorityName="Fauvel MS (Jolivet" authorityYear="1957" box="[301,424,1461,1485]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stenomela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caledonica">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FEDE5ED36689FA58" box="[301,424,1461,1485]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">caledonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not without analogy to the preceding (
<figureCitation id="130623E8FFC2FFA7FC975ED364E0FA58" box="[868,961,1461,1485]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–12" captionStartId="22.[151,257,1927,1948]" captionTargetBox="[222,1365,204,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-78@22.[208,1377,195,1899]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 5–12. Bohumiljania species, dorsal: 5, B. aoupinie sp. nov., male; 6, B. humboldti Jolivet, Verma &amp; Mille, female; 7, B. lafoa sp. nov., male; 8, B. mandjelia sp. nov., male; 9, B. tango sp. nov., female; 10, B. xanthogramma sp nov., female; 11, B. xaracuu sp. nov., female; 12, B. yuaga sp. nov., female. Scale bar = 10mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig 11B</figureCitation>
) [refers to description of wing of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFC2FFA7FAB25ED36658FA64" authority="Erichson" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1847" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stenomela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FAB25ED3662EFA64" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Stenomela pallida</emphasis>
Erichson
</taxonomicName>
on pp. 58–9]
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFC2FFA7FF345E9B6493F914" blockId="7.[151,1436,1281,1809]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Wing large (15x 
<quantity id="4CC59288FFC2FFA7FE895E9B6698F980" box="[378,441,1533,1557]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="5.0">5mm</quantity>
), more chitinous than the preceeding. Costal, radial, 
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FBF95E98633CF980" box="[1034,1053,1534,1557]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">rt</emphasis>
identical. 
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FB645E9B63EAF980" box="[1175,1227,1533,1557]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">M1a</emphasis>
identical but more chitinous with 
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FEB35D44667EF9AC" box="[320,351,1570,1593]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">rm</emphasis>
apparent [
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FE2A5D4466D9F9AC" box="[473,504,1570,1593]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">rm</emphasis>
described as invisible in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFC2FFA7FCE85D4764A9F9AC" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1847" box="[795,904,1569,1593]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stenomela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FCE85D4764A9F9AC" box="[795,904,1569,1593]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">S. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]. Distal and median [veins] identical but more chitinous. Cubito-anal system almost identical, of purely eumolpine form, well chitinised. [cell] 
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FB0A5D236203F9C8" box="[1273,1314,1605,1629]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">an1</emphasis>
lenticular, sinuous, elongated; 
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FE855D0F66BEF914" box="[374,415,1641,1665]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">an2</emphasis>
subquadrangular; 
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FD835D0F65AEF914" box="[624,655,1641,1665]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">3A</emphasis>
clear, sinuous, elongated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFC2FFA7FF345DE86336F884" blockId="7.[151,1436,1281,1809]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
It is equally noted that this aberrant eumolpine, like the preceding genus [
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFC2FFA7FC095DEB634FF930" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1847" box="[1018,1134,1677,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stenomela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FC095DEB634FF930" box="[1018,1134,1677,1701]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Stenomela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
], does not have the mediocubital fleck [
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FEC75DD76651F95C" box="[308,368,1713,1737]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">tache</emphasis>
]. In its place is only a fleck [
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FD315DD765DFF95C" box="[706,766,1713,1737]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">tache</emphasis>
, same word as preceeding!] more chitinous, diffuse, rather large, reaching the posterior border of the wing, of a totally different structure from the medio-cubital fleck of eumolpines. It is simply a coloured zone of the wing without special structure.”
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFC2FFA7FF645C276210F8CC" blockId="7.[151,1436,1857,2025]" box="[151,1329,1857,1881]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Translation of the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFC2FFA7FDF65C2764BEF8CC" authority="Monros, 1958" authorityName="Monros" authorityYear="1958" box="[517,927,1857,1881]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antiqua">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFC2FFA7FDF65C2765DBF8CC" box="[517,762,1857,1881]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Bohumiljania antiqua</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC429CFFC2FFA7FCF15C2764BEF8CC" author="Monros" box="[770,927,1857,1881]" firstAuthor="Monros" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="143 - 153" refId="ref21750" refString="Monros, F. (1958) Considerationes sobre la fauna del Sur de Chile y revision de la tribus Stenomelini (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae). Acta zoologica Lilloana, 15, 143 - 153." type="journal article" year="1958">Monrós, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(pages 149–150) [see 
<figureCitation id="130623E8FFC2FFA7FB6F5C276204F8CC" box="[1180,1317,1857,1881]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="21.[151,258,1906,1927]" captionTargetBox="[189,1408,187,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-73@21.[179,1408,183,1882]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Bohumiljania caledonica (Jolivet). Figs 1–3, reproductions of original drawings of the holotype by Monrós (1958): 1, head &amp; pronotum; 2, ventral, with antenna; 3, lateral. Reproduced from Acta Zoologica Lilloana. Fig. 4, reproduction of original drawing of the wing of the holotype (Jolivet 1957). Reproduced from Mémoires de l’Institut royale des Sciences naturelles de Belgique." pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figures 1–3</figureCitation>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFC2FFA7FF345C036610F87C" blockId="7.[151,1436,1857,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
“Length 
<quantity id="4CC59288FFC2FFA7FEDA5C036655F8E8" box="[297,372,1893,1917]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="14.0">14mm</quantity>
. Humeral width 
<quantity id="4CC59288FFC2FFA7FDDD5C03654AF8E8" box="[558,619,1893,1917]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="5.0">5mm</quantity>
. Body elongate-oval, moderately convex in transverse section and a little convex in longitudinal section. Colouration chestnut-brown, unicolourous. Antennae, mandibles and distal half of femora, tibiae and tarsi black [whether the distal half of all these is black, or just the femora, is not clear in the original Spanish].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFCDFFA8FF345BF16316FEAA" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,607]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Head with fine and dense punctures between the eyes, sparser on the clypeus. Face dorsally glabrous. Venter of face with decumbent fine and slightly dense setae, absent from medial area. Head with slight longitudinal depression between eyes. Antennal tubercles almost absent. Internal edge of eyes feebly sinuate. Six basal antennomeres shining and glabrous; antennomeres decreasing in length from 3–6 and increasing in length from 6–8 (from 8 the antenna is broken). Apex of right mandible trifid, with median tooth longest.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFCDFFA8FF345A2A6443FDCA" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,607]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Pronotum slightly transverse, anterior edge subtruncate and posterior edge with moderately developed scutellar lobe. Sides with short expansion in the middle of the anterior. Pronotum with larger punctures than head, but sparser, punctures completely absent from posterior region of disc. Anterior discal region with a small oval depression (an accident to the specimen?). Pronotal base, on both sides of median lobe, with an elongated depression, short but deep. Prosternal intercoxal process as wide as length of first trochanter, with sides parallel and continuing in line with side of bilobed apex. Elytra impunctate, glabrous, smooth and shining. Mesosternum protruding slightly between mid coxae. Metasternal intercoxal lobe with short and broad tip. Tibiae with stronger and denser setae [than face]. Venter of tarsi densely and compactly setose.”</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFCDFFA8FF6459E9633CFD32" blockId="8.[151,1437,655,1328]" box="[151,1053,655,679]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Additional descriptive information from illustrations provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC429CFFCDFFA8FC8A59E96338FD32" author="Monros" box="[889,1049,655,679]" firstAuthor="Monros" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="143 - 153" refId="ref21750" refString="Monros, F. (1958) Considerationes sobre la fauna del Sur de Chile y revision de la tribus Stenomelini (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae). Acta zoologica Lilloana, 15, 143 - 153." type="journal article" year="1958">Monrós, 1958</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFCDFFA8FF3459D266E1FD7A" blockId="8.[151,1437,655,1328]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">In his taxonomic work, Monrós provided drawings, slightly stylised but generally accurate, showing surface sculpture as well as shape.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFCDFFA8FF34599A6229FAA5" blockId="8.[151,1437,655,1328]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The illustrations accompanying the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCDFFA8FCFE599A6327FC81" authorityName="Monros" authorityYear="1958" box="[781,1030,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antiqua">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FCFE599A6327FC81" box="[781,1030,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bohumiljania antiqua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC429CFFCDFFA8FBE4599A6397FC81" author="Monros" box="[1047,1206,764,788]" firstAuthor="Monros" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="143 - 153" refId="ref21750" refString="Monros, F. (1958) Considerationes sobre la fauna del Sur de Chile y revision de la tribus Stenomelini (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae). Acta zoologica Lilloana, 15, 143 - 153." type="journal article" year="1958">Monrós 1958</bibRefCitation>
: figs 2, 3, 6; reproduced here as 
<figureCitation id="130623E8FFCDFFA8FEC45879669CFCA2" box="[311,445,799,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="21.[151,258,1906,1927]" captionTargetBox="[189,1408,187,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-73@21.[179,1408,183,1882]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Bohumiljania caledonica (Jolivet). Figs 1–3, reproductions of original drawings of the holotype by Monrós (1958): 1, head &amp; pronotum; 2, ventral, with antenna; 3, lateral. Reproduced from Acta Zoologica Lilloana. Fig. 4, reproduction of original drawing of the wing of the holotype (Jolivet 1957). Reproduced from Mémoires de l’Institut royale des Sciences naturelles de Belgique." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figures 1–3</figureCitation>
) provide the following additional information: postantennal tubercles impunctate; genal lobe short, about equal to minimum length of gena; gula defined by anterior transverse groove; 9 antennomeres present (! – perhaps the drawing antedated the description), 2 shortest, 6 slightly longer than 2 and clearly shorter than all others, 7 longest, 7–9 each longer than each of 1–6; last maxillary palpomere fusiform; pronotum elevated towards apex in lateral view; pronotal sides entirely margined, sinuate in lateral view; anterior angles laterally projecting; posterior angles not projecting, approximately 90°; pronotal anterior not margined except near angles, base without margination at middle; large circular area of pronotal disc impunctate, about half pronotal width and 2/3 length; hypomeron setose; sides of prosternal anterior densely punctured and setose; prosternal process impunctate and glabrous, without median groove, almost parallel-sided, angle at apex U-shaped, c. 45°; elytral epipleuron thin throughout, not elevated at humerus; mesoventrite lobe abruptly raised; sides of mesoventrite and mesanepisternum and mesepimeron densely punctured; middle of metaventrite impunctate and glabrous with almost complete discrimen, sides sparsely punctured, with short setae; anterior intercoxal lobe slightly elevated in lateral view; tarsomeres not greatly elongated (but drawn in oblique view, so difficult to assess); tarsal claws simple; ventrites glabrous and impunctate at middle, moderately closely setose at sides; first ventrite with possible femoral plica (indicated in ventral view but not in lateral); last ventrite almost semi-circular, longer than pre-apical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFCDFFA8FF645E0667F9FAE2" blockId="8.[151,1436,1376,2012]" box="[151,216,1376,1399]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFCDFFA8FF345EE26475F9E1" blockId="8.[151,1436,1376,2012]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The description given by Monrós should be sufficient to distinguish this species, especially the combination of pronotal grooves and lateral swellings, lack of punctures on basal half of pronotal disc, small oval depression rather than elevation on anterior of disc, reddish-brown colour, glabrous impunctate elytra and glabrous impunctate prosternal process. The apex of the abdomen illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC429CFFCDFFA8FCE35E966498F99D" author="Monros" box="[784,953,1520,1544]" firstAuthor="Monros" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="143 - 153" refId="ref21750" refString="Monros, F. (1958) Considerationes sobre la fauna del Sur de Chile y revision de la tribus Stenomelini (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae). Acta zoologica Lilloana, 15, 143 - 153." type="journal article" year="1958">Monrós (1958)</bibRefCitation>
is rounded, suggesting a female; if so, the male is likely to be significantly shorter, as in other species of the genus, perhaps 
<quantity id="4CC59288FFCDFFA8FBEC5D726346F9B9" box="[1055,1127,1556,1580]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="12.0">12mm</quantity>
or less. However, Monrós’ illustrations may not be totally reliable as they show the epipleuron narrow at the humerus and a possible femoral plica, neither of which occur in any other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFCDFFA8FF345DE66260F8E5" blockId="8.[151,1436,1376,2012]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Jolivet’s wing description includes presence of a coloured medial fleck, but the colour is not indicated. However, the illustrated wing has only slight indication of this fleck (
<figureCitation id="130623E8FFCDFFA8FC9A5DC264EBF929" box="[873,970,1700,1724]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="21.[151,258,1906,1927]" captionTargetBox="[189,1408,187,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-73@21.[179,1408,183,1882]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Bohumiljania caledonica (Jolivet). Figs 1–3, reproductions of original drawings of the holotype by Monrós (1958): 1, head &amp; pronotum; 2, ventral, with antenna; 3, lateral. Reproduced from Acta Zoologica Lilloana. Fig. 4, reproduction of original drawing of the wing of the holotype (Jolivet 1957). Reproduced from Mémoires de l’Institut royale des Sciences naturelles de Belgique." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figure 4</figureCitation>
), therefore it seems reasonable to assume it is not dark and distinct. We have examined wings of the eight 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCDFFA8FC9F5DAE637CF975" box="[876,1117,1736,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FC9F5DAE6325F975" box="[876,1028,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bohumiljania</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
available to us and they differ slightly in degree of darkening of the radial veins and the membrane surface including the medial fleck. In species with pale wings the variation may be intraspecific. The fleck is uncoloured in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCDFFA8FBC45C7763AEF8BD" authorityName="Reid &amp; Beatson" authorityYear="2011" box="[1079,1167,1808,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lafoa">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FBC45C7763AEF8BD" box="[1079,1167,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. lafoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="130623E8FFCDFFA8FB6C5C7663D3F8BD" box="[1183,1266,1808,1832]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–74" captionStartId="29.[151,257,1929,1950]" captionTargetBox="[244,1326,223,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@29.[231,1349,180,1888]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 69–74. Bohumiljania species. Figs 69–70, lateral of pronotum: 69, B. lafoa sp. nov.; 70, B. xaracuu sp. nov. Figs 71–72, apex of elytra: 71, B. aoupinie sp. nov.; 72, B. humboldti Jolivet, Verma &amp; Mille. Figs 73–74, base of wing, with medial fleck indicated: 73, B. lafoa sp. nov.; 74, B. yuaga sp. nov." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCDFFA8FAF55C7762B4F8BD" authorityName="Reid &amp; Beatson" authorityYear="2011" box="[1286,1429,1808,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandjelia">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FAF55C7762B4F8BD" box="[1286,1429,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. mandjelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCDFFA8FF645C5367D6F8D9" authorityName="Reid &amp; Beatson" authorityYear="2011" box="[151,247,1845,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tango">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FF645C5367D6F8D9" box="[151,247,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. tango</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCDFFA8FEDC5C5366D9F8D9" authorityName="Reid &amp; Beatson" authorityYear="2011" box="[303,504,1844,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthogramma">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FEDC5C5366D9F8D9" box="[303,504,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. xanthogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, slightly yellowish in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCDFFA8FD045C5364A8F8D9" box="[759,905,1844,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humboldti">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FD045C5364A8F8D9" box="[759,905,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. humboldti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCDFFA8FC6B5C536309F8D9" authorityName="Reid &amp; Beatson" authorityYear="2011" box="[920,1064,1844,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandjelia">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FC6B5C536309F8D9" box="[920,1064,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. mandjelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCDFFA8FB925C5363FCF8D9" authorityName="Reid &amp; Beatson" authorityYear="2011" box="[1121,1245,1845,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xaracuu">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FB925C5363FCF8D9" box="[1121,1245,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. xaracuu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and brown in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCDFFA8FA775C5367D8F8FA" authorityName="Reid &amp; Beatson" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aoupinie">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FA775C5367D8F8FA" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. aoupinie</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCDFFA8FEDC5C3F66B3F8E5" authorityName="Reid &amp; Beatson" authorityYear="2011" box="[303,402,1881,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yuaga">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FEDC5C3F66B3F8E5" box="[303,402,1881,1904]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. yuaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="130623E8FFCDFFA8FE515C3E66D7F8E5" box="[418,502,1880,1904]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–74" captionStartId="29.[151,257,1929,1950]" captionTargetBox="[244,1326,223,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-70@29.[231,1349,180,1888]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 69–74. Bohumiljania species. Figs 69–70, lateral of pronotum: 69, B. lafoa sp. nov.; 70, B. xaracuu sp. nov. Figs 71–72, apex of elytra: 71, B. aoupinie sp. nov.; 72, B. humboldti Jolivet, Verma &amp; Mille. Figs 73–74, base of wing, with medial fleck indicated: 73, B. lafoa sp. nov.; 74, B. yuaga sp. nov." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
). Jolivet’s description does not provide colour, therefore it is undiagnostic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFCDFFA8FF345C1A663AF82D" blockId="8.[151,1436,1376,2012]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
In a recent paper, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC429CFFCDFFA8FE645C1A6559F801" author="Jolivet" box="[407,632,1916,1940]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Jolivet" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="3 - 22" refId="ref21586" refString="Jolivet, P., Verma, K. K. &amp; Mille, C. (2003) Biology and taxonomy of Bohumiljania caledonica (Jolivet) (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae). Nouvelle Revue d'Entomologie, 20 (1), 3 - 22." type="journal article" year="2003">
Jolivet 
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FE195C1B653CF801" box="[490,541,1916,1940]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. (2003)
</bibRefCitation>
describe the 
<typeStatus id="548681CFFFCDFFA8FCE15C1A6455F801" box="[786,884,1916,1940]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
as black, which conflicts with Monros’ original description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823F6DFFCDFFA9FF345CA2632EFE8C" blockId="8.[151,1436,1376,2012]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,151,317]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCDFFA8FF345CA266C2F849" authorityName=": Jolivet, Verma &amp; Mille" authorityYear="2003" box="[199,483,1988,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caledonica">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCDFFA8FF345CA266C2F849" box="[199,483,1988,2012]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bohumiljania caledonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a specimen labelled ‘Nouvelle Caledonie’. The claim that this species was rediscovered in 2002 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC429CFFCCFFA9FDEF5BF165CBFF3A" author="Jolivet" box="[540,746,151,176]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Jolivet" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="3 - 22" refId="ref21586" refString="Jolivet, P., Verma, K. K. &amp; Mille, C. (2003) Biology and taxonomy of Bohumiljania caledonica (Jolivet) (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae). Nouvelle Revue d'Entomologie, 20 (1), 3 - 22." type="journal article" year="2003">
Jolivet 
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCCFFA9FD835BFF6588FF25" box="[624,681,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
) was based on the assumption that only one species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCCFFA9FAA45BFE67D5FF46" authorityName="Monros" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCCFFA9FAA45BFE67D5FF46" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Bohumiljania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
existed on the 
<quantity id="4CC59288FFCCFFA9FE585BDD66DBFF46" box="[427,506,187,211]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="km" value="300.0">300km</quantity>
long main island of 
<collectingCountry id="F32A7FFDFFCCFFA9FD025BDD6487FF46" box="[753,934,187,211]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
. As noted above, the authors also ignored numerous gross differences between the original description and their material, such as colour, sculpture and shape. We have therefore described Jolivet 
<emphasis id="B949E37FFFCCFFA9FDDD5A646547FE8C" box="[558,614,257,281]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
’s species as new (see under 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D44EEFFCCFFA9FC555A6464DEFE8C" authorityName="Reid &amp; Beatson" authorityYear="2011" box="[934,1023,257,281]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bohumiljania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lafoa">
